 Basic Scans

nmap <target>                    Default scan (top 1000 ports)
nmap -p- <target>                 All 65535 ports
nmap -p 80,443,22 <target>        Specific ports
nmap -sV <target>                 Service version detection
nmap -O <target>                  OS detection
nmap -A <target>                 Aggressive: OS, version, scripts, traceroute


Scan Types


nmap -sS <target>   SYN (stealth) scan — default with root
nmap -sT <target>    TCP connect scan — no root required
nmap -sU <target>    UDP scan
nmap -sN <target>    Null scan
nmap -sF <target>   FIN scan
nmap -sX <target>    Xmas scan
```

Speed / Timing

nmap -T0    Paranoid (slowest)
nmap -T3   Normal (default)
nmap -T4   Aggressive
nmap -T5   Insane (fastest, noisy)


Output Formats

nmap -oN output.txt     Normal text
nmap -oX output.xml     XML
nmap -oG output.gnmap   Grepable
nmap -oA output         All formats


NSE Scripts

nmap --script=default <target>
nmap --script=vuln <target>
nmap --script=http-enum <target>
nmap --script=smb-vuln* <target>

 Useful Combos


Full recon
nmap -A -T4 -p- -oN full_scan.txt <target>

Quick port discovery then deep scan
nmap -p- --min-rate 5000 <target>
nmap -A -p <open_ports> <target>
